details.name: Infantry
details.text: (staitc) This is an emergency! (crackle) Is anyone out there? We need help!

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: This is General Cyrus, we can hear you, just barely. What happened here? Where is Blake?

details.name: Infantry
details.text: It's so good to hear you, Sir. We were conducting an assault on Ruby Dusk positions, but it all went south. We lost comms with Commando Blake, he must have pushed through.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: He left you behind?

details.name: Infantry
details.text: We don't know. He went on ahead, we were securing his back, right until we lost comms. After that we got swamped with Ruby Dusk units, barely managed to fall back to safe positions.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: This is a fine mess. What is your current situation

details.name: Infantry
details.text: We are holed up in a forest. Thich bushes provided us cover so far, but we can hear them searching for us, enemy must be close.

details.name: Infantry
details.text: There is a second concealed group way ahead. They have some heavy equipment with them.

details.name: Infantry
details.text: We think there are other valuable units hidden somewhere as well.

details.name: Infantry
details.text: Ruby Dusk is holding this key town, you have to capture this position if you hope to proceed.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: Recon suggested that it is not too heavily fortified.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: They appear to be moving north, in order to set up a permanent base there. From the looks of it, it did not happen yet, which means they can't reinforce.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: That was the good news. The bad news is that we have not managed to set up camp either. These units are all I have for this mission.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: Air support is back up, which means I am able to call in paratroopers using my Deep Strike ability. Just have to keep in mind, that resources are going to be very limited.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: Which means that rescuing those stranded soldiers is my top priority. They will join the fight once one of my units approaches their position.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: Finally, destroying all Ruby Dusk forces is essential before we can move on.
Rescue Sapphire Dawn forces.
Defeat Ruby Dusk forces.
General Cyrus must survive.
(Optional) Rescue advanced units.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: I have made a tactical mistake! Fall back!

details.name: Infantry
details.text: Time to move, guys!

details.name: Soldier #1
details.text: I swear I have seen someone over there.

details.name: Soldier #2
details.text: We've been out here for hours, there is no one here. Let's just go back.

details.name: Soldier #1
details.text: You know we can't go back without finding these marauders. Just watch that road.

details.name: Soldier #2
details.text: Hey! I think someone is coming!

details.name: Attack Helicopter
details.text: Hey, help is here! Starting the engine. Hop on board and we can take you back to the town.

details.name: Soldier
details.text: Sapphire Dawn spotted, and a lot of them! Where did they come from?

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: That garrison is strong, but we will manage. Just one more fight before this day ends.

details.name: Rocket Artillery
details.text: So good to see you! We're kinda stuck here. Give us a push and we can help.

details.name: Infantry
details.text: Road secured, Sir!

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: Get engineering crew over here and set up a base. You deserve some rest before we move on.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: I wonder what happened with Blake. How could he abandon his troops like that? I have to question him when I have a chance.

details.name: Tank
details.text: Locked and loaded, let's smoke these Ruby Dusk punks.
